<div><h3>ENG 182 - African American Literature I </h3>  <hr>Addresses major periods and principal authors of the African American canon. Readings may cover a historical span that could range from the 18th century to the present or could represent focused concern with select authors and/or a given literary movement. Students are expected to gain a historically as well as a culturally contextual appreciation of the literature produced by writers of African descent in the Americas. For undergraduate English majors and minors, this course satisfies the Historical Sequence (B-1) requirement. Meets the Historical Perspective (HP).<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> HP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Every year<br><br></div>		</td>
